    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A common base class for sub-renderobjects that are combined into the proper features. <computeroutput>ObjectType</computeroutput> is the underlying datamodel object that stores the mesh, e.g. <computeroutput><ref refid="classMR_1_1ObjectMesh" kindref="compound">ObjectMesh</ref></computeroutput>. <computeroutput>RenderObjectType</computeroutput> is the underlying render object, e.g. <computeroutput><ref refid="classMR_1_1RenderMeshObject" kindref="compound">RenderMeshObject</ref></computeroutput>. If <computeroutput>IsPrimary</computeroutput> is true, the visual properties are copied from the target datamodel object. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
